==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sharpie
<hw>Sharp"ie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
long, sharp, flat-bottomed boat, with one or two masts carrying a
triangular sail. They are often called <altname>Fair Haven
sharpies</altname>, after the place on the coast of Connecticut where
they originated.</def> <mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sharpling</ent>⟦br⟧
